The agent needs to write a C program that mimics `/app/cleaner_oracle`.
The oracle reads `int32_t`, if the value is `-9999` it outputs a float NaN (`0x7FC00000`), otherwise it outputs `(float)val * 0.0625f`.

Verifier kind: fuzz_equivalence
Oracle path: `/app/cleaner_oracle`
Fuzz-input distribution: Random 32-bit signed integers, uniformly distributed, length ranging from 0 to 100,000 integers. N = 50 test cases.
Agent's expected entry point: `/home/user/cleaner` reading from stdin and writing to stdout.

Fixture kind: stripped_binary
Binary path: `/app/cleaner_oracle`
High-level algorithm:
```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdint.h>
#include <math.h>

int main() {
    int32_t val;
    uint32_t nan_bits = 0x7FC00000;
    float nan_val = *((float*)&nan_bits);

    while (fread(&val, sizeof(int32_t), 1, stdin) == 1) {
        float out;
        if (val == -9999) {
            out = nan_val;
        } else {
            out = (float)val * 0.0625f;
        }
        fwrite(&out, sizeof(float), 1, stdout);
    }
    return 0;
}
```
The binary `/app/cleaner_oracle` is compiled from the above C code with `gcc -O2 -s`.

